Django-Serialize
================

### Introduction

Django-Serialize extends the default Django serialization framework, inspired by wadofstuff (https://code.google.com/p/wadofstuff/wiki/DjangoFullSerializers). It is designed to give the developer more control over how models are serialized and make it possible to change serialized objects based on context.

Django-Serialize focuses on extending Django Models to return a serializable dictionary object. The output of this object can be customized on a per model basis.

To begin, simple add the SerializeMixin to one of your models: